oop review rule is already established process, not an open planning gap.\n- Keep the rule-level safety result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that containment-first version safety is established process, not an open planning gap.\n- Keep the rule-level isolation result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that mailbox state stays isolated from legacy board/tab metadata, so rollback remains straightforward.\n- Keep the rule-level opt-in result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that team-mode surfaces remain additive and secondary, not replacements for existing single-thread flows.\n- Keep the rule-level non-regression result fixed: the mailbox task plan now reflects that current mailbox work has stayed non-destructive across thread lifecycle, board interaction, auto-continue, and loop-control surfaces.\n- Keep the rule-layer cleanup result fixed: for the current mailbox scope, rule-level process and safety debt is effectively closed; remaining unresolved work is execution hardening plus later delivery hygiene.\n- Keep the analysis-convergence result fixed: further analysis-only repo edits are no longer justified unless a new regression or containment need appears.\n- Keep the post-convergence result fixed: repeated analysis after convergence has not surfaced any new regression, so the remaining critical-path work is still the Task 6 resolver slice.\n- Keep the post-convergence discipline fixed: analysis-only mailbox passes should stop mutating task-plan or active-plan scope unless a new regression, drift signal, or containment need appears.\n- Keep the forced-analysis discipline fixed: if a caller keeps requiring another analysis-only mailbox pass without new evidence, limit repo edits to a minimal handoff refresh and preserve the same execution target.\n- Keep the repeated-analysis refresh discipline fixed: when such a minimal refresh is unavoidable, only restate the same Task 6 resolver handoff instead of reopening task-plan scope or adding new mailbox branches.\n- Keep the unchanged-handoff summary fixed: without new regression, drift, or containment evidence, repeated analysis-only mailbox passes are bookkeeping only; they must not create new scope, branches, boundaries, or targets, and the same Task 6 resolver slice remains the only actionable next step until execution changes the state.\n- Keep the active-plan dedup result fixed: now that the unchanged-handoff state is summarized once, later analysis-only passes should preserve that compressed handoff shape unless new evidence requires a real plan change.\n- Keep the active-plan growth guard fixed: analysis-only mailbox passes should not grow `ACTIVE_PLAN.md` again unless a new regression, drift signal, or containment requirement creates a materially different handoff.\n- Keep the active-plan edit floor fixed: when no new evidence exists, any forced analysis-only update to `ACTIVE_PLAN.md` should stay at the level of a minimal guard or bookkeeping line and must not change the substantive Task 6 handoff.\n- Keep the active-plan substantive freeze fixed: absent new evidence, later analysis-only mailbox passes should leave the substantive Task 6 handoff block unchanged and only record stability, not reshape the plan.\n- Keep the analysis-only stability record fixed: when the mailbox review window stays clean, future analysis-only passes should record that stability and preserve the same hardening handoff rather than inventing fresh planning work.\n- Keep the same-handoff carry-through fixed: when the review window stays clean, repeated analysis-only passes should continue carrying the same Task 6 handoff forward instead of generating alternate mailbox directions.\n- Keep the same-hardening summary fixed: when the review window stays clean, every equivalent description of the remaining mailbox work should collapse back to the same single bounded Task 6 resolver slice plus its follow-up syntax check, without creating alternate targets, paths, tracks, la